name: 5-(4-morpholinyl)-2-nitrophenol
Reason: 5-Morpholinyl is a bulky group which introduces a rigid structure with increased molecular weight. Each morpholinyl group can be estimated to add approximately +20 to +30°C due to the increase in molecular weight and rigidity of the structure. The nitro group also introduces a significant dipole, increasing intermolecular forces and melting point by approximately +50°C. The ketone group can also contribute to the melting point due to its ability to form hydrogen bonds, estimated at around +20°C.
